WEBVTT

00:06.441 --> 00:06.919
Previously on
"Just Add Magic"...

00:07.007 --> 00:08.399
Bitter Truth Truffles.

00:08.486 --> 00:10.314
I bet they make people
tell the truth.

00:10.401 --> 00:12.012
[gasping]

00:12.099 --> 00:13.839
That truffle's not nearly
as tasty as it looks.

00:13.926 --> 00:15.319
Not your best work.

00:15.406 --> 00:16.886
Hannah: The first truffle
puts you under a spell,

00:16.973 --> 00:18.496
and the second one
breaks it.

00:18.583 --> 00:19.802
I'm going to
run for mayor.

00:19.889 --> 00:21.238
Wow, Mom, that's huge.

00:21.325 --> 00:22.631
May the best person win.

00:22.718 --> 00:25.634
That mall of yours
is about to get
a new restaurant.

00:25.721 --> 00:27.157
Fine, but you gotta
do something for me.

00:27.244 --> 00:29.638
I'm going to get
the mayor's endorsement,
don't worry.

00:29.725 --> 00:31.553
Find dirt on Terri.

00:31.640 --> 00:33.511
Check out the old
main library records.

00:33.598 --> 00:35.339
I think you'll find
what you're looking for.

00:35.426 --> 00:38.342
Kelly:
Hannah, your teacher is
the third protector.

00:38.429 --> 00:39.952
Hannah:
What I don't get is why
he's cursing people.

00:40.040 --> 00:42.259
Kelly: Not people,
protectors.

00:42.346 --> 00:44.044
- Mr. Morris:
You're dangerous.
- Huh?

00:44.131 --> 00:47.395
You are the ones
cursing everyone in town
to forget magic.

00:49.310 --> 00:51.834
What?

00:51.921 --> 00:55.142
We're not cursing people
to forget magic, you are.

00:55.229 --> 00:57.361
Why would you even
think that?

00:57.448 --> 00:59.146
Uh, because you have
a creepy folder

00:59.233 --> 01:00.886
full of names of
former protectors,

01:00.973 --> 01:03.193
and the ones who've
forgotten magic
have been crossed out.

01:03.280 --> 01:05.587
I was just keeping track of
the people that you cursed.

01:05.674 --> 01:08.851
After everything I've done
to un-curse my grandma,

01:08.938 --> 01:11.680
why would I
curse her again?

01:11.767 --> 01:14.291
Fine. Maybe you aren't
behind it,

01:14.378 --> 01:16.598
but you are still
irresponsible with
the magic.

01:16.685 --> 01:19.383
Hey, we do not use
the magic irresponsibly.

01:19.470 --> 01:21.298
Oh, really?
Where shall I begin?

01:21.385 --> 01:23.779
How about
magically locking me in
this house all night.

01:23.866 --> 01:25.259
And you,
Miss Parker-Kent,

01:25.346 --> 01:27.348
you came to school
under some kind of
attention spell,

01:27.435 --> 01:29.393
and then for your most
egregious use of magic,

01:29.480 --> 01:31.178
you froze the entire town.

01:31.265 --> 01:32.222
How do you know that?

01:32.309 --> 01:33.397
Are you denying it?

01:33.484 --> 01:35.573
I can see why Mr. Morris
intimidates you.

01:35.660 --> 01:37.358
That was to save
my grandma.

01:37.445 --> 01:39.708
Maybe you spelled
Noelle and RJ

01:39.795 --> 01:42.145
so that you were
the only protector
who remembers magic.

01:42.232 --> 01:43.625
Oh, that is
a lovely theory, Hannah,

01:43.712 --> 01:45.192
but for the fact that
I'm not a protector.

01:47.411 --> 01:48.673
You're not?

01:48.760 --> 01:50.893
But we saw a picture of you
with RJ and Noelle

01:50.980 --> 01:52.199
together in high school.

01:52.286 --> 01:55.724
Yeah, I knew them,
but I wasn't a protector.

01:55.811 --> 01:58.335
Wait, if you weren't
a protector,
how were you involved?

01:58.422 --> 01:59.902
[school bell rings]

01:59.989 --> 02:02.905
Mr. Morris: I was the one
keeping them out of trouble.

02:02.992 --> 02:04.994
They were always
in detention.

02:05.081 --> 02:06.691
RJ was the prankster
of the group.

02:11.392 --> 02:12.871
Then there was Noelle,

02:12.958 --> 02:14.743
who loved taking shortcuts.

02:19.748 --> 02:22.142
And then there was
Caroline.

02:22.229 --> 02:25.710
She was the ringleader,
rebellious and reckless.

02:25.797 --> 02:28.235
She was all trouble.

02:28.322 --> 02:30.672
Why were you in detention,
Mr. Morris?

02:30.759 --> 02:33.065
For writing
Caroline's essay.

02:33.153 --> 02:34.415
I'm not proud of it,

02:34.502 --> 02:36.982
but back then
we were friends.

02:37.069 --> 02:38.767
Or at least
I thought we were.

02:38.854 --> 02:42.945
Mr. Morris, if you're not
erasing people's memories
of magic,

02:43.032 --> 02:44.947
and we're not,

02:45.034 --> 02:46.209
then it has to be Caroline.

02:48.994 --> 02:50.909
That does make sense.

02:52.650 --> 02:53.651
Except for one thing.

02:53.738 --> 02:55.784
What's that?

02:55.871 --> 02:57.002
After we graduated
high school,

02:57.089 --> 02:59.614
Caroline
completely disappeared.

02:59.701 --> 03:01.485
No one has seen or heard
from her in...

03:01.572 --> 03:02.399
nearly 20 years.

03:06.142 --> 03:08.971
♪♪

03:14.716 --> 03:16.500
What's wrong?

03:16.587 --> 03:19.851
Mayor Davies
announced her support
for Adam Lever.

03:19.938 --> 03:22.724
Your former boss?
But she loves you.

03:22.811 --> 03:24.073
Not anymore.

03:24.160 --> 03:25.814
Man, there is nothing
I didn't do for that woman.

03:25.901 --> 03:27.207
I mean,
I wrote her speeches,

03:27.294 --> 03:29.339
I organized her
pancake breakfasts.

03:29.426 --> 03:31.167
I even fed her fish
when she went out of town.

03:31.254 --> 03:32.864
Lever's gotta be
behind this.

03:32.951 --> 03:35.563
I agree.
Maybe it's time to
fight fire with fire.

03:35.650 --> 03:37.086
We've been over this.

03:37.173 --> 03:39.567
I'm just gonna
prepare really hard for
the debate tomorrow,

03:39.654 --> 03:40.916
and let the voters decide.

03:48.706 --> 03:50.186
Excuse me,
Mr. Morris.

03:50.273 --> 03:51.448
Do you have a second?

03:51.535 --> 03:52.928
Is this about
your last paper?

03:53.015 --> 03:54.669
It's about Caroline.

03:54.756 --> 03:56.279
Should I be concerned
about my paper?

03:56.366 --> 03:57.759
Relax.

03:57.846 --> 03:59.935
You did fine.

04:00.022 --> 04:01.023
You're very smart,
Hannah.

04:01.110 --> 04:03.765
And perhaps I've been
extra hard on you.

04:03.852 --> 04:06.681
Because I'm a...
[whispers] protector?

04:06.768 --> 04:08.204
I was testing
your character.

04:08.291 --> 04:09.858
Well, I hope I passed.

04:09.945 --> 04:13.165
Because I take my job as
a protector very seriously.

04:13.253 --> 04:14.732
I'm beginning to believe you.

04:14.819 --> 04:16.212
You're certainly
more qualified
to be a protector

04:16.298 --> 04:18.606
- than Caroline ever was.
- All three of us are.

04:18.692 --> 04:20.521
That's why we're
working so hard to
solve this mystery

04:20.608 --> 04:22.653
before anyone else
can get hurt.

04:22.740 --> 04:25.003
Can you tell me how
you got so involved?

04:25.090 --> 04:27.310
[sighs] Well, um,

04:27.397 --> 04:29.878
at the risk of
sounding immodest,

04:29.965 --> 04:32.184
I was the smartest kid
in school.

04:32.272 --> 04:34.491
One day, they came
running up to me for help.

04:34.578 --> 04:36.885
They had a big problem
on their hands.

04:36.972 --> 04:38.974
Arthur. So, okay,
the three of us
have this cookbook

04:39.061 --> 04:41.063
with crazy recipes and spices
no one's every heard of,

04:41.150 --> 04:42.456
and RJ wouldn't stop
talking about it,

04:42.543 --> 04:44.327
so Noelle and I cooked
a Shut Him Up Shortcake
recipe,

04:44.414 --> 04:45.763
and now RJ can't talk
and I can't stop,

04:45.850 --> 04:47.548
and it's really crazy
'cause I feel like--

04:47.635 --> 04:49.071
You've gotta help us
undo this.

04:49.158 --> 04:50.551
I don't mind
RJ not talking,

04:50.638 --> 04:53.205
but Caroline is
driving me crazy.

04:53.293 --> 04:56.165
I noticed the riddle.
The others completely
ignored it.

04:56.252 --> 04:58.341
"Be warned,
whenever adding
cedronian spice,

04:58.428 --> 04:59.734
"whatever results
will come with a price."

04:59.821 --> 05:01.213
"...will come with
a price."

05:01.301 --> 05:02.780
Been there, done that.

05:02.867 --> 05:05.174
So, how'd you break
the spell?

05:10.222 --> 05:12.050
Did you add the
cedronian vanilla
to the cake?

05:12.137 --> 05:13.574
Yeah, so what?
What's the big deal--

05:13.661 --> 05:15.227
You need to help that kid
pick his stuff up.

05:15.315 --> 05:17.621
No way.
He needs to learn not to
shove so much stuff in his--

05:17.708 --> 05:19.797
Come on.
Help the kid out.

05:19.884 --> 05:21.190
He's new.
Remember your first day?

05:25.150 --> 05:26.630
Hey, you're new, right?
I'm Caroline.

05:26.717 --> 05:28.284
Let me give you a hand.

05:28.371 --> 05:30.808
Where'd you move from?
Welcome to Lavender Heights.

05:30.895 --> 05:31.853
You should
hang out with us.

05:31.940 --> 05:34.464
Come on, dude,
get my voice ba--

05:34.551 --> 05:35.639
- [sighs]
- What?

05:35.726 --> 05:36.727
You can talk again.

05:36.814 --> 05:38.990
You're a genius.

05:42.907 --> 05:45.214
You put together that
Caroline needed to help
that boy

05:45.301 --> 05:47.172
in order to break
the cedronian downside.

05:47.259 --> 05:49.827
Both: "With a noble act
from a heart that's true."

05:49.914 --> 05:51.307
Very impressive.

05:51.394 --> 05:53.527
Yeah, I figured that
they would learn from
that mistake,

05:53.614 --> 05:55.529
and be more careful
in the future.

05:55.616 --> 05:58.053
I couldn't have been
more wrong.

05:58.140 --> 06:01.012
But how is any of this
gonna help you find Caroline?

06:01.099 --> 06:02.971
I'm not sure.

06:03.058 --> 06:04.320
Yet.

06:07.062 --> 06:08.672
Jake came up with
a special menu

06:08.759 --> 06:10.457
for your mom's
after-debate party.

06:10.544 --> 06:12.850
Take a look.

06:12.937 --> 06:16.288
"Terri-Yaki Skewers"
and "Win-Ter Vegetables."

06:16.376 --> 06:17.768
Clever.
She's gonna love it.

06:17.855 --> 06:20.380
This kid.
He's very creative.

06:20.467 --> 06:21.816
Ah, I learned from
the best.

06:21.903 --> 06:24.949
It's nice to see you
and Mama P so close again.

06:25.036 --> 06:26.647
Again?
Mama P's the coolest.

06:27.909 --> 06:29.911
Not always.

06:29.998 --> 06:32.392
No, Jill, this is just
not my style.

06:32.479 --> 06:34.611
Be smart, Terri.
The goal is to win here.

06:34.698 --> 06:36.613
What's going on?

06:36.700 --> 06:38.354
These are some
not so nice things

06:38.441 --> 06:39.834
Lever did over the summer.

06:39.921 --> 06:41.313
But your mom
isn't interested.

06:41.401 --> 06:42.358
Well, I am.

06:44.534 --> 06:47.494
"Lever closed the public pool
for his son's birthday party

06:47.581 --> 06:49.321
"during the heat wave."

06:49.409 --> 06:53.108
"Lever cut down
a 100 year old oak tree
to expand his driveway."

06:53.195 --> 06:56.241
- That's terrible.
- No, I told you guys.

06:56.328 --> 06:58.330
I'm just sticking to
the issues.

07:01.638 --> 07:03.423
Can I be honest?

07:03.510 --> 07:06.208
I'm worried my mom's
gonna lose the debate.

07:06.295 --> 07:08.210
I'm worried your mom's
gonna lose the election.

07:11.431 --> 07:13.476
I don't get it.
They were clearly
bad protectors.

07:13.563 --> 07:15.217
Why did the book
even choose them?

07:15.304 --> 07:17.219
Maybe it's because
Grandma threw the book
over the falls

07:17.306 --> 07:18.742
before it was ready
to move on.

07:18.829 --> 07:20.875
And she did use
her morbium seed.

07:20.962 --> 07:22.920
That could have really
messed things up.

07:23.007 --> 07:24.356
Darbie: We need to know
more about Caroline.

07:24.444 --> 07:26.402
How else are we
gonna find her?

07:26.489 --> 07:28.622
Maybe we could talk to
Mr. Morris at the debate.

07:28.709 --> 07:30.624
Don't remind me
about the debate.

07:30.711 --> 07:32.321
Pretty sure my mom's
gonna get roasted.

07:35.803 --> 07:37.239
What if we cook
the Bitter Truth Truffles

07:37.326 --> 07:38.414
and give them to Lever?

07:38.501 --> 07:40.068
It'll force him to
tell the truth.

07:40.155 --> 07:43.375
Kelly,
that sounds like something
the old '90s trio would do.

07:43.463 --> 07:45.900
You know,
the ones that we just said
were bad protectors?

07:45.987 --> 07:47.554
But my mom deserves to win.

07:47.641 --> 07:49.991
Yes, but not with magic.

07:52.036 --> 07:53.647
How about we make
the truth truffles,

07:53.734 --> 07:56.824
and give them to
Lever and Mrs. Q?

07:56.911 --> 07:59.914
That does technically
make things fair.

08:00.001 --> 08:02.133
My mom's already
being honest, so sure.

08:02.220 --> 08:04.527
Let's do it.

08:04.614 --> 08:07.443
♪♪

08:09.000 --> 08:15.074
